The paper explores trust in Automated Machine Learning (AutoML) systems, which involves the use of AI methods to generate and optimize machine learning models. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also investigates the information needs of data scientists for establishing trust in AutoML systems, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) considerations. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of transparency features in AutoML tools, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) practices.
